article.description: Isaiah Williams had 19 points, 10 rebounds and six assists to help Iona hold off Drexel for a 77-70 win Monday night.
article.headline: Williams scores 19 as Iona holds off Drexel for 77-70 win
article.linkText: Williams scores 19 as Iona holds off Drexel for 77-70 win
article.story: NEW ROCHELLE, N.Y. -- Isaiah Williams had 19 points, 10 rebounds and six assists to help Iona hold off Drexel for a 77-70 win Monday night. Jordan Washington scored 15, Deyshonee Much had 11 points and Jahaad Proctor added 10 for Iona (5-6). Washington scored nine points during a 25-4 run that gave the Gaels a 19-point lead midway through the first half. Drexel (2-9) used a 12-2 spurt that spanned halftime to pull within eight on a 3-pointer by Sammy Mojica with 17 minutes to play, but Iona scored 15 of the next 19 to make it 58-39 with 11:04 left. A pair of free throws by Tavon Allen capped a 13-3 Drexel run and cut the Dragons' deficit to 72-70 with 1:38 remaining, but Iona made 5 of 8 free throws from there to seal it. Drexel missed its last field goal attempts. Mojica led the Dragons with a career-high tying 20 points.
